article.headline: Princeton 64, Concordia, N.Y. 44
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Douglas Davis scored 11 points to lead Princeton to a 64-44 win over Concordia, N.Y. on Sunday. Marcus Schroeder added nine points -- all on 3-pointers -- and pulled down eight rebounds for the Tigers (5-8). Samuel Batista had 15 points and seven rebounds for the Clippers (5-14), while Kenny Gaskins finished with 10 points and nine boards. After Concordia opened the game with a 5-0 run, Princeton went ahead for good with an 18-4 run midway through the first half. The Tigers led 32-19 at the break and then maintained double-digit leads for most of the second half. Concordia won the battle of the boards, outrebounding Princeton 40-33.
